@ToivoAdams yup, it's complaining because when you "rebase" you are re-writing history. When you try to push it's out of sync with the branch you're pushing to and it tells you to "pull" in order to be coordinated. By doing a "force push", you're saying "forget whatever the current state of the branch is, what I'm pushing is correct".

This is very nice when you're doing it to your own branch/PR but it's pretty self-explanatory how bad it could be doing to the Apache repo.

I'm gonna take a look at the new PR now. Feel free to close this one whenever you're able.

